sentences: Caitlin Rose (born June 23, 1987) is a country singer from Nashville, Tennessee.
Rose was previously the lead singer of Nashville indie band Save Macaulay, on local label Theory 8 until 2007.
As a solo artist, she signed to BMI in 2008.
The title track of her seven-track 2008 EP, Dead Flowers, is a cover of a Rolling Stones song.
She was born in Dallas, Texas, and her family moved to Nashville in 1994.
She attended community college in Nashville for a year before leaving to focus on music.
